# Token burn controls (Cursor + repo)

## Agent behavior (Cursor chat)

- Prefer **short** answers; avoid repeating long rules or prior turns unless the user asked for a recap.
- **Do not** paste multi-hundred-line files or full JSON dumps unless requested; use **summaries**, **line ranges**, or **grep**.
- Batch tool reads; avoid redundant searches.

## Repo controls (Student Ollama — lab hosts)

Optional caps are implemented in **`renaissance_v4/game_theory/token_burn_guards_v1.py`** and wired into **`student_ollama_student_output_v1`**.

Enable on the host when conserving Ollama/compute tokens::

```bash
export BLACKBOX_TOKEN_BURN_GUARD=1
# optional:
# export BLACKBOX_STUDENT_PROMPT_JSON_MAX_CEILING=32000
# export BLACKBOX_OLLAMA_NUM_PREDICT_MAX=1536
```

Default remains **guard off** so existing behavior is unchanged unless this env is set.
